## Description {#details}

This file defines a set of templates that efficiently compute a dominator tree over a generic graph.

This is used typically in LLVM for fast dominance queries on the CFG, but is fully generic w.r.t. the underlying graph types.

Unlike ADT/&#42; graph algorithms, generic dominator tree has more requirements on the graph&#39;s NodeRef. The NodeRef should be a pointer and, either NodeRef-&gt;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/analysis/basicaliasanalysis-cpp/#a1b8850f1ed44c12bc3501175a71c251c">getParent()</a> must return the parent node that is also a pointer or DomTreeNodeTraits needs to be specialized.

FIXME: Maybe GenericDomTree needs a TreeTraits, instead of GraphTraits.

<Link id="l00578" /><CodeLine lineNumber="578"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// API to update (Post)DominatorTree information based on modifications to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00579" /><CodeLine lineNumber="579"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// the CFG...</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00580" /><CodeLine lineNumber="580"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00581" /><CodeLine lineNumber="581"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Inform the dominator tree about a sequence of CFG edge insertions and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00582" /><CodeLine lineNumber="582"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// deletions and perform a batch update on the tree.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00583" /><CodeLine lineNumber="583"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00584" /><CodeLine lineNumber="584"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// This function should be used when there were multiple CFG updates after</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00585" /><CodeLine lineNumber="585"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// the last dominator tree update. It takes care of performing the updates</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00586" /><CodeLine lineNumber="586"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// in sync with the CFG and optimizes away the redundant operations that</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00587" /><CodeLine lineNumber="587"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// cancel each other.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00588" /><CodeLine lineNumber="588"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// The functions expects the sequence of updates to be balanced. Eg.:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00589" /><CodeLine lineNumber="589"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///  - &#123;&#123;Insert, A, B&#125;, &#123;Delete, A, B&#125;, &#123;Insert, A, B&#125;&#125; is fine, because</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00590" /><CodeLine lineNumber="590"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///    logically it results in a single insertions.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00591" /><CodeLine lineNumber="591"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///  - &#123;&#123;Insert, A, B&#125;, &#123;Insert, A, B&#125;&#125; is invalid, because it doesn&#39;t make</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00592" /><CodeLine lineNumber="592"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///    sense to insert the same edge twice.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00593" /><CodeLine lineNumber="593"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00594" /><CodeLine lineNumber="594"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// What&#39;s more, the functions assumes that it&#39;s safe to ask every node in the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00595" /><CodeLine lineNumber="595"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// CFG about its children and inverse children. This implies that deletions</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00596" /><CodeLine lineNumber="596"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// of CFG edges must not delete the CFG nodes before calling this function.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00597" /><CodeLine lineNumber="597"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00598" /><CodeLine lineNumber="598"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// The applyUpdates function can reorder the updates and remove redundant</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00599" /><CodeLine lineNumber="599"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// ones internally (as long as it is done in a deterministic fashion). The</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00600" /><CodeLine lineNumber="600"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// batch updater is also able to detect sequences of zero and exactly one</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00601" /><CodeLine lineNumber="601"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// update -- it&#39;s optimized to do less work in these cases.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00602" /><CodeLine lineNumber="602"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00603" /><CodeLine lineNumber="603"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Note that for postdominators it automatically takes care of applying</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00604" /><CodeLine lineNumber="604"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// updates on reverse edges internally (so there&#39;s no need to swap the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00605" /><CodeLine lineNumber="605"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// From and To pointers when constructing DominatorTree::UpdateType).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00606" /><CodeLine lineNumber="606"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// The type of updates is the same for DomTreeBase&lt;T&gt; and PostDomTreeBase&lt;T&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00607" /><CodeLine lineNumber="607"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// with the same template parameter T.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00608" /><CodeLine lineNumber="608"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00609" /><CodeLine lineNumber="609"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// \\param Updates An ordered sequence of updates to perform. The current CFG</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00610" /><CodeLine lineNumber="610"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// and the reverse of these updates provides the pre-view of the CFG.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00611" /><CodeLine lineNumber="611"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00612" /><CodeLine lineNumber="612" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dominatortreebase/#a470b5b573c7915fe13bd529b22c9adbc"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">void</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dominatortreebase/#a470b5b573c7915fe13bd529b22c9adbc">applyUpdates</a>(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/arrayref">ArrayRef&lt;UpdateType&gt;</a> Updates) &#123;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00891" /><CodeLine lineNumber="891"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// verify - checks if the tree is correct. There are 3 level of verification:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00892" /><CodeLine lineNumber="892"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///  - Full --  verifies if the tree is correct by making sure all the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00893" /><CodeLine lineNumber="893"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///             properties (including the parent and the sibling property)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00894" /><CodeLine lineNumber="894"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///             hold.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00895" /><CodeLine lineNumber="895"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///             Takes O(N^3) time.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00896" /><CodeLine lineNumber="896"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00897" /><CodeLine lineNumber="897"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///  - Basic -- checks if the tree is correct, but compares it to a freshly</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00898" /><CodeLine lineNumber="898"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///             constructed tree instead of checking the sibling property.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00899" /><CodeLine lineNumber="899"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///             Takes O(N^2) time.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00900" /><CodeLine lineNumber="900"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00901" /><CodeLine lineNumber="901"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///  - Fast  -- checks basic tree structure and compares it with a freshly</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00902" /><CodeLine lineNumber="902"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///             constructed tree.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00903" /><CodeLine lineNumber="903"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///             Takes O(N^2) time worst case, but is faster in practise (same</span></CodeLine>
